Spec: SpecDD Plan Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in planning code, docs, tests, refactors, tasks, or spec changes under existing SpecDD contracts.

Owns:
  ./specdd-plan/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-plan/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Trigger planning only when the user asks for a plan or when unclear scope, authority, public contracts, risk, or verification would make immediate implementation unsafe.
  Resolve target scope, bootstrap files, effective spec chain, and write authority.
  Summarize the target scope and applicable spec chain.
  Identify files or specs likely to change.
  Identify relevant `Must`, `Must not`, `Forbids`, `Scenario`, `Tasks`, and `Done when` constraints.
  Identify verification likely needed, blockers, conflicts, and risks.
  Propose the smallest safe implementation sequence.
  Produce a practical plan without editing files.
  Wait for the user to approve or revise the plan before implementation.

Must not:
  Delay ordinary authorized implementation by treating every SpecDD change as needing a plan first.
  Propose work that violates active `Must not`, `Forbids`, or authority constraints.
  Propose broad refactors or new contracts unless the active specs or user request require them.
  Present unclear write authority as safe implementation scope.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
